Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim and chop the @aubergine{1}(trimmed and chopped into 2cm pieces). Pop the pieces
onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer.

Roast the aubergine until golden brown and soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

Meanwhile, add @water{200%ml} and @vegetable stock{1%sachet}(stock powder) to a
#pot{} and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{100%grams} and pop a
#lid{} on the pot.

Leave aside for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

While the couscous cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1%unit}(halved and core and seeds
discarded). Chop into 2cm chunks.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%grams}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the pepper until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: By stirring only every so often you'll allow the pepper to pick up a nice
> colour.

Add the @diced Irish chicken breast{260%grams}(diced) to the pan and season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Fry until chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the chicken to the pan and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to vacuum packing we use to keep it fresh.

Reduce the heat to medium-high.

Add the @chopped tomato with onion & garlic{1%pack} and half the parsley to the
pan.

Cover and simmer until chicken is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}, adding
a splash of @water{to taste} to loosen the sauce if necessary.

Once cooked, stir through the roasted aubergine.

Serve the chicken stew on a bed of fluffy couscous.

Drizzle over a little @balsamic glaze{2%sachets}.

Finish with a sprinkling of parsley and pepper.